{
  "text": "9-11 GM-CSF supports the survival and expansion of MDSCs in the tumor microenvironment. [CITATION_1] The sources of GM-CSF include tumors and activated immune effectors such as T cells, natural killer (NK) cells, and DCs. IL-1\u03b2 recruits MDSCs; mice inoculated with tumor cells secreting IL-1\u03b2 exhibit elevated levels of MDSCs. IL-1\u03b2-induced MDSCs have elevated levels of reactive oxygen species with enhanced T-cell suppression. [CITATION_2] Furthermore, IL-6 secreted by tumors increases the frequency of MDSCs in tumors.",
  "correct_citation": {
